AspNetWebSocketContext Class

Definition

Provides a base class that represents contextual details about an individual AspNetWebSocket request.

In this Article

public abstract class AspNetWebSocketContext : System.Net.WebSockets.WebSocketContext
Inheritance
Object
System.Net.WebSockets.WebSocketContext
AspNetWebSocketContext

AspNetWebSocketContext()

When implemented in a derived class, initializes a new instance of the AspNetWebSocketContext class.

protected AspNetWebSocketContext ();

Properties

AnonymousID

Gets the anonymous-user identifier for the current AspNetWebSocket connection.

public virtual string AnonymousID { get; }
Value
String

The identifier for the anonymous user.

Value

A reference to the application state.

The property is not implemented.

Gets the root virtual path of the host ASP.NET application.

public virtual string ApplicationPath { get; }
Value
String

The path of the application.

NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Cache

The property is not implemented.

ClientCertificate

Gets the certificate that a remote client issues in response to the server's request for the client's identity.

public virtual System.Web.HttpClientCertificate ClientCertificate { get; }
Value
HttpClientCertificate

A string that represents the binary stream of the certificate's content in ASN.1 format.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

ConnectionCount

Gets the number of active WebSocket connections.

public static int ConnectionCount { get; }
Value
Int32

The number of active WebSocket connections.

CookieCollection

Returns the stem.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocketContext.Cookies* collection typed as a CookieCollection for Windows applications that use cookies based on the Cookie class (such as WCF server applications).

public override System.Net.CookieCollection CookieCollection { get; }
Value
CookieCollection

The collection of cookies.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Cookies

Gets the collection of cookies that was sent by a remote client in an AspNetWebSocket message.

public virtual System.Web.HttpCookieCollection Cookies { get; }
Value
HttpCookieCollection

The collection of cookies.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

FilePath

Gets the virtual path of the requested file.

public virtual string FilePath { get; }
Value
String

The virtual path.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Remarks

As an example of a virtual path, for the URL http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail, the value of this property is /virdir/page.html.

Headers

Gets the collection of headers that was sent by a remote client.

public override System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection Headers { get; }
Value
NameValueCollection

The collection of message headers.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

IsAuthenticated

Gets a value that indicates whether a message from a remote client has been authenticated.

public override bool IsAuthenticated { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if the message has been authenticated; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

IsClientConnected

Gets a value that indicates whether the client is connected to the server.

public virtual bool IsClientConnected { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if the client is connected; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

IsDebuggingEnabled

Gets a value that indicates whether the application that hosts the current AspNetWebSocket connection is running in ASP.NET debug mode.

public virtual bool IsDebuggingEnabled { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if the application is in debug mode; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

IsLocal

Gets a value that indicates whether an AspNetWebSocket message was sent from the local computer.

public override bool IsLocal { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if the message is from the local computer; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

IsSecureConnection

Gets a value that indicates whether the AspNetWebSocket connection uses the WebSocket Secure protocol (WSS).

public override bool IsSecureConnection { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if the connection uses WSS; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Items

When overridden in a derived class, gets a key/value collection that can be used to share data between a module and a handler during an AspNetWebSocket request.

public virtual System.Collections.IDictionary Items { get; }
Value
IDictionary

The key/value collection.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

LogonUserIdentity

Gets the security token for the current user.

public virtual System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity LogonUserIdentity { get; }
Value
WindowsIdentity

An object that provides identity information to IIS about the current user.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Origin

Gets the origin of the WebSocket connection.

public override string Origin { get; }
Value
String

The origin of the WebSocket connection.

Path

Gets the virtual path of the requested resource.

public virtual string Path { get; }
Value
String

The virtual path.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Remarks

As an example of a virtual path, for the URL http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail, the value of this property is /virdir/page.html/tail.

PathInfo

Gets additional path information for a resource that has a URL extension.

public virtual string PathInfo { get; }
Value
String

A string that contains additional path information for a resource.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Remarks

As an example of a virtual path, for the URL http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail, the value of this property is /tail.

Profile

Gets an object that contains user profile data.

public virtual System.Web.Profile.ProfileBase Profile { get; }
Value
ProfileBase

A ProfileBase object if the application configuration file contains a definition for the profile's properties; otherwise, null.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

QueryString

Gets the collection of query string variables from an AspNetWebSocket message that was sent by the client.

public virtual System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection QueryString { get; }
Value
NameValueCollection

The collection of query string variables that was sent by the client. For example, if the request URL is http://www.contoso.com/default.aspx?id=44, this property returns a collection that contains a single item whose value is id=44.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

RawUrl

Gets the portion of a URL that follows the website name in an AspNetWebSocket message that was sent by the client.

public virtual string RawUrl { get; }
Value
String

The part of the URL that follows the website name. For example, if the complete request URL is http://www.contoso.com/default.aspx?id=44, the value of this property is /default.aspx?id=44.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

RequestUri

Gets the original Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of an AspNetWebSocket message that was sent by the client.

public override Uri RequestUri { get; }
Value
Uri

The original URI.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

SecWebSocketKey

Gets the encrypted key that is sent in the handshake request to establish an AspNetWebSocket connection.

public override string SecWebSocketKey { get; }
Value
String

The encrypted key.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

SecWebSocketProtocols

Gets a list of application-level protocols (subprotocols) that a client can use to send messages using an AspNetWebSocket connection.

public override System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable<string> SecWebSocketProtocols { get; }
Value
IEnumerable<String>

The list of subprotocols, separated by spaces.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

SecWebSocketVersion

Gets the version of the WebSocket protocol that an AspNetWebSocket connection must use.

public override string SecWebSocketVersion { get; }
Value
String

The specified version of the WebSocket protocol.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Server

Gets the HttpServerUtility object that provides methods that are used in processing requests.

public virtual System.Web.HttpServerUtilityBase Server { get; }
Value
HttpServerUtilityBase

The HttpServerUtility object that provides methods that are used in processing requests.

ServerVariables

Gets a name/value collection of variables that provide information about the web server and about the current AspNetWebSocket connection.

public virtual System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection ServerVariables { get; }
Value
NameValueCollection

The collection of server variables.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Timestamp

Gets the timestamp of an AspNetWebSocket message that was sent by the client.

public virtual DateTime Timestamp { get; }
Value
DateTime

The timestamp.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Unvalidated

Gets unvalidated versions of one or more field values that are submitted in an AspNetWebSocket message.

public virtual System.Web.UnvalidatedRequestValuesBase Unvalidated { get; }
Value
UnvalidatedRequestValuesBase

The unvalidated values.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

Remarks

An unvalidated value has not been checked by ASP.NET request validation and might contain markup, script, or reserved characters. For more information about request validation, see UnvalidatedRequestValues.

UrlReferrer

Gets a collection of URI data about the message that was sent by the client prior to the current message.

public virtual Uri UrlReferrer { get; }
Value
Uri

The URI data.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

User

Gets an object that represents the security context of the user for the current AspNetWebSocket connection.

public override System.Security.Principal.IPrincipal User { get; }
Value
IPrincipal

The security context of the user.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

UserAgent

Gets the name of the remote client.

public virtual string UserAgent { get; }
Value
String

The browser name and version.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

UserHostAddress

Gets the IP address of the remote client.

public virtual string UserHostAddress { get; }
Value
String

The IP address.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

UserHostName

Gets the DNS name of the remote client.

public virtual string UserHostName { get; }
Value
String

The DNS name.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

UserLanguages

Gets the collection of language preferences for the remote client.

public virtual string[] UserLanguages { get; }
Value
String[]

The client language preferences.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.

WebSocket

Gets a reference to the current AspNetWebSocket instance.

public override System.Net.WebSockets.WebSocket WebSocket { get; }
Value
WebSocket

The current AspNetWebSocket instance.

Exceptions
NotImplementedException

The property is not implemented.
